All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Client
    Client class implements an interface for a simple Client app that communicates with the server via TCP sockets in a string based IO.
    ClientIdentifier
    Stores an identification of a Client connected via socket to manage a download request.
    Config
    Loads out the config.cnf file to a class that separates all the parameters.
    ContentDB
    Stores methods and data from the server Content data-base.
    DateAndTime
    To get the current time as a string.
    DownloadRequestsBuffer
    Implements a buffer of download requests in order to set up a MAX_DOWN downloads for the server requests.
    FileSharingSystem
    Main business Class that stores all the methods that implement all the logic operations on the data stored on the system.
    GeneralMessage
    Shows an error/hint/warning message as a formatted text to show on console.
    GUI
    Methods to show GUI interfaces to client.
    Input
    Implements method to read standard Java types, like strings, ints,...
    MetaData
    Metadata class implements a music object properties such as title, artist,...
    Music
    Music class implements a music object that stores its properties and its id.
    Server
    Server class implements the server operating on a host and waiting for connections on a certain port.
    ServerApp
    Main Server app that loads the config, server socket and runs the server.
    ServerWorker
    Handles the clients that connect to the server and parses its messages through the socket.
    User
    User class implements a user for the system given its credentials, name and password.
    UsersDB
    Stores the Users of the system and the logic around them.
